# Publishing

- Never publish manually from a local machine. All releases must go through CI via a GitHub Release, which triggers the publish workflow automatically.
- This ensures published artifacts always match the state of `main`, and credentials never touch developer machines.

## To release

1. Ensure all changes are merged to `main`
2. Create a GitHub Release: `gh release create v<VERSION> --title "v<VERSION>" --notes "..."`
3. The publish workflow fires automatically — no manual Gradle commands needed
